tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE successful_phishing_attacks (
    attack_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    attacker_ip VARCHAR NOT NULL,
    victim_email VARCHAR NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE peak_engagement_times (
    engagement_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    engagement_type VARCHAR NOT NULL,
    engagement_duration INTERVAL NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE phishing_analysis (
    analysis_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    attack_id INT NOT NULL,
    engagement_id INT NOT NULL,
    analysis_result TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE phishing_locations (
    location_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    location_name VARCHAR NOT NULL,
    geo_location VARCHAR NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE successful_phishing_attacks (
    attack_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    attack_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    attacker_ip VARCHAR(255),
    victim_email VARCHAR(255),
    engagement_duration INTERVAL
);
